  "texts": [
    "Strictly, to realise the Wakimoto construction, we only need to bosonize the (ξ +, η -) system and thus κ 1 need not be introduced.",
    "The stated realisation of the Wakimoto fields does not live in the \"large Hilbert space\" that includes the zero mode of e iκ 1, whilst they do depend on the zero mode of e -iκ 2.",
    "This is why only the background charge for κ 2 affects the correlation functions of Wakimoto fields.",
    "16 Φ is charged under κ 2 and therefore has a conformal anomaly, so we do need to take care of the κ 2 background charge.",
    "Put another way, we identify the κ 2 conformal anomaly as the source of the radial conformal anomaly in the Wakimoto representation and so we shall place an associated background charge at z * a."
  ],
